## Coding Style

### DO ‚úÖ
- Use latest syntax (satisfies, using, const type parameters)
- Prefer arrow functions and const
- Use async/await, never callbacks
- Destructure everything
- Use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??)
- Single responsibility, small functions
- Named exports (tree-shaking)
- Use fetch (native), not axios for new code
- CSS-in-JS with Tailwind or Panda CSS
- Use Biome config instead of .eslintrc

### DON'T ‚ùå
- No long comments or JSDoc (types are docs)
- No "TODO" comments (make GitHub issue or fix now)
- No console.log in production code
- No any type (use unknown or proper types)
- No var, only const/let
- No classes unless really needed (functional > OOP)
- No legacy packages (check bundlephobia first)
- No .prettierrc if using Biome

